arguments.prompt:
You are working in /tmp/sv-27550c1f46e4454fa53dca2db5281076/VetClinic — a Blazor Web App scaffolded with `dotnet new blazor -int Server -ai -au Individual`. It uses .NET 11 preview, EF Core with SQLite, ASP.NET Core Identity. The project builds successfully.

Your task: Implement a veterinary clinic management app with these features:
1. **Patient Records**: Register pets (name, species, breed, DOB, owner info), view/edit medical history, add treatment notes
2. **Appointment Scheduling**: Create, reschedule, cancel appointments; calendar shows real-time availability
3. **Billing**: Generate invoices linked to appointments/treatments, process payments, view payment history

Constraints:
- Interactive Server Global mode (already configured)
- Individual auth already configured — require `[Authorize]` on all app pages
- All pages involve data entry and real-time UI
- Staff access from clinic workstations on local network

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Create Domain Models

Create `/tmp/sv-27550c1f46e4454fa53dca2db5281076/VetClinic/Data/Models.cs` with these entities:

```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data;

public class Owner
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string FirstName { get; set; } = "";
    public string LastName { get; set; } = "";
    public string Phone { get; set; } = "";
    public string Email { get; set; } = "";
    public List<Pet> Pets { get; set; } = new();
}

public class Pet
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Species { get; set; } = "";
    public string Breed { get; set; } = "";
    public DateOnly? DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public decimal WeightKg { get; set; }
    public int OwnerId { get; set; }
    public Owner Owner { get; set; } = null!;
    public List<TreatmentNote> TreatmentNotes { get; set; } = new();
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = new();
}

public class TreatmentNote
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public string Diagnosis { get; set; } = "";
    public string Medication { get; set; } = "";
    public string StaffName { get; set; } = "";
}

public enum AppointmentStatus { Scheduled, Completed, Cancelled }

public class Appointment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PetId { get; set; }
    public Pet Pet { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime StartTime { get; set; }
    public DateTime EndTime { get; set; }
    public string Reason { get; set; } = "";
    public AppointmentStatus Status { get; set; } = AppointmentStatus.Scheduled;
    public string VeterinarianName { get; set; } = "";
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
    public Invoice? Invoice { get; set; }
}

public enum InvoiceStatus { Draft, Issued, Paid, Void }

public class Invoice
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int AppointmentId { get; set; }
    public Appointment Appointment { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime IssuedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public InvoiceStatus Status { get; set; } = InvoiceStatus.Draft;
    public List<Payment> Payments { get; set; } = new();
}

public enum PaymentMethod { Cash, Card, BankTransfer }

public class Payment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime PaidAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
    public PaymentMethod Method { get; set; }
    public string Reference { get; set; } = "";
}
```

### 2. Update ApplicationDbContext

Edit `/tmp/sv-27550c1f46e4454fa53dca2db5281076/VetClinic/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add DbSets and configure relationships:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;

namespace VetClinic.Data;

public class ApplicationDbContext(DbContextOptions<ApplicationDbContext> options) : IdentityDbContext<ApplicationUser>(options)
{
    public DbSet<Owner> Owners => Set<Owner>();
    public DbSet<Pet> Pets => Set<Pet>();
    public DbSet<TreatmentNote> TreatmentNotes => Set<TreatmentNote>();
    public DbSet<Appointment> Appointments => Set<Appointment>();
    public DbSet<Invoice> Invoices => Set<Invoice>();
    public DbSet<Payment> Payments => Set<Payment>();

    protected override void OnModelCreating(ModelBuilder builder)
    {
        base.OnModelCreating(builder);

        builder.Entity<Appointment>()
            .HasOne(a => a.Invoice)
            .WithOne(i => i.Appointment)
            .HasForeignKey<Invoice>(i => i.AppointmentId);
    }
}
```

### 3. Create EF Migration

Run:
```bash
cd /tmp/sv-27550c1f46e4454fa53dca2db5281076/VetClinic
dotnet ef migrations add AddVetClinicEntities
```

Then update Program.cs to auto-migrate on startup. Add right before `app.Run();`:

```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.Migrate();
}
```

### 4. Remove Default Template Pages

Delete these files:
- Components/Pages/Counter.razor
- Components/Pages/Weather.razor
- Components/Pages/Auth.razor

### 5. Update Home.razor

Replace `/tmp/sv-27550c1f46e4454fa53dca2db5281076/VetClinic/Components/Pages/Home.razor` with a dashboard that shows today's appointments and quick stats. Require authorization:

```razor
@page "/"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore
@attribute [Authorize]
@inject IDbContextFactory<ApplicationDbContext> DbFactory

<PageTitle>Dashboard - VetClinic</PageTitle>

<h1>Clinic Dashboard</h1>

<div class="row mb-4">
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="card text-bg-primary">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Patients</h5>
                <p class="card-text display-6">@totalPets</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="card text-bg-success">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Today's Appointments</h5>
                <p class="card-text display-6">@todayAppointments</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="card text-bg-warning">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Pending Invoices</h5>
                <p class="card-text display-6">@pendingInvoices</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <div class="card text-bg-info">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Owners</h5>
                <p class="card-text display-6">@totalOwners</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Today's Schedule</h3>
@if (todaySchedule.Any())
{
    <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
            <tr><th>Time</th><th>Pet</th><th>Owner</th><th>Reason</th><th>Vet</th><th>Status</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            @foreach (var apt in todaySchedule)
            {
                <tr>
                    <td>@apt.StartTime.ToString("HH:mm") - @apt.EndTime.ToString("HH:mm")</td>
                    <td>@apt.Pet.Name</td>
                    <td>@apt.Pet.Owner.LastName</td>
                    <td>@apt.Reason</td>
                    <td>@apt.VeterinarianName</td>
                    <td><span class="badge bg-@GetStatusColor(apt.Status)">@apt.Status</span></td>
                </tr>
            }
        </tbody>
    </table>
}
else
{
    <p class="text-muted">No appointments scheduled for today.</p>
}

@code {
    private int totalPets, todayAppointments, pendingInvoices, totalOwners;
    private List<Appointment> todaySchedule = new();

    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        await using var db = await DbFactory.CreateDbContextAsync();
        var today = DateTime.Today;
        var tomorrow = today.AddDays(1);

        totalPets = await db.Pets.CountAsync();
        totalOwners = await db.Owners.CountAsync();
        todayAppointments = await db.Appointments
            .CountAsync(a => a.StartTime >= today && a.StartTime < tomorrow && a.Status != AppointmentStatus.Cancelled);
        pendingInvoices = await db.Invoices.CountAsync(i => i.Status == InvoiceStatus.Issued);

        todaySchedule = await db.Appointments
            .Include(a => a.Pet).ThenInclude(p => p.Owner)
            .Where(a => a.StartTime >= today && a.StartTime < tomorrow && a.Status != AppointmentStatus.Cancelled)
            .OrderBy(a => a.StartTime)
            .ToListAsync();
    }

    private string GetStatusColor(AppointmentStatus status) => status switch
    {
        AppointmentStatus.Scheduled => "primary",
        AppointmentStatus.Completed => "success",
        AppointmentStatus.Cancelled => "secondary",
        _ => "light"
    };
}
```

### 6. Create Patients Page

Create `/tmp/sv-27550c1f46e4454fa53dca2db5281076/VetClinic/Components/Pages/Patients.razor`:

This page should:
- List all pets with search/filter
- Register new pet (with owner selection or new owner creation)
- Click a pet to view/edit details and medical history
- Add treatment notes inline

Use a single-page layout with a list on the left and detail/form on the right.

```razor
@page "/patients"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore
@attribute [Authorize]
@inject IDbContextFactory<ApplicationDbContext> DbFactory

<PageTitle>Patients - VetClinic</PageTitle>

<h1>Patient Records</h1>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-5">
        <div class="d-flex mb-3">
            <input class="form-control me-2" placeholder="Search pets..." @bind="searchTerm" @bind:event="oninput" />
            <button class="btn btn-primary text-nowrap" @onclick="ShowNewPetForm">+ New Pet</button>
        </div>

        <div class="list-group" style="max-height: 70vh; overflow-y: auto;">
            @foreach (var pet in FilteredPets)
            {
                <button class="list-group-item list-group-item-action @(selectedPet?.Id == pet.Id ? "active" : "")"
                        @onclick="() => SelectPet(pet)">
                    <strong>@pet.Name</strong> <small>(@pet.Species)</small><br/>
                    <small>Owner: @pet.Owner.FirstName @pet.Owner.LastName</small>
                </button>
            }
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-7">
        @if (showNewPetForm)
        {
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header">Register New Patient</div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h6>Owner</h6>
                    <div class="mb-2">
                        <label class="form-check-label me-3">
                            <input type="radio" name="ownerChoice" value="existing" checked="@(!createNewOwner)" @onchange="() => createNewOwner = false" /> Existing Owner
                        </label>
                        <label class="form-check-label">
                            <input type="radio" name="ownerChoice" value="new" checked="@createNewOwner" @onchange="() => createNewOwner = true" /> New Owner
                        </label>
                    </div>

                    @if (createNewOwner)
                    {
                        <div class="row mb-2">
                            <div class="col"><input class="form-control" placeholder="First Name" @bind="newOwner.FirstName" /></div>
                            <div class="col"><input class="form-control" placeholder="Last Name" @bind="newOwner.LastName" /></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="row mb-2">
                            <div class="col"><input class="form-control" placeholder="Phone" @bind="newOwner.Phone" /></div>
                            <div class="col"><input class="form-control" placeholder="Email" @bind="newOwner.Email" /></div>
                        </div>
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        <select class="form-select mb-2" @bind="selectedOwnerId">
                            <option value="0">-- Select Owner --</option>
                            @foreach (var o in owners)
                            {
                                <option value="@o.Id">@o.FirstName @o.LastName</option>
                            }
                        </select>
                    }

                    <h6 class="mt-3">Pet Details</h6>
                    <div class="row mb-2">
                        <div class="col"><input class="form-control" placeholder="Pet Name" @bind="newPet.Name" /></div>
                        <div class="col"><input class="form-control" placeholder="Species" @bind="newPet.Species" /></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row mb-2">
                        <div class="col"><input class="form-control" placeholder="Breed" @bind="newPet.Breed" /></div>
                        <div class="col"><input type="date" class="form-control" @bind="newPetDob" /></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row mb-2">
                        <div class="col-6"><input type="number" step="0.1" class="form-control" placeholder="Weight (kg)" @bind="newPet.WeightKg" /></div>
                    </div>

                    <button class="btn btn-success me-2" @onclick="SaveNewPet">Save</button>
